@davidbau i dont think this will be correct.
Remember that conda does not ship CuDNN headers or NCCL headers, only .so files.
So what will end up happening is that your header will come from system paths (like /usr/local/cuda) and lib will come from conda.

body:
@davidbau i dont think this will be correct.
Remember that `conda` does not ship CuDNN headers or NCCL headers, only .so files.

So what will end up happening is that your header will come from system paths (like `/usr/local/cuda`) and lib will come from `conda`.
